The paper deals with planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on qualitative numerical planning, which involves manipulating non-negative real variables, making it relevant to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper also discusses complexity and reductions, which are topics in logic and verification (cs.LO) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a generate-and-test algorithm, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
